Because `peek()` accepts a `Consumer`.&lt;br&gt;
A `Consumer` is designed to accept argument but returns no result. &lt;br&gt;

For example here :

    genre.stream().peek(s-&gt; s.replace(&quot;r&quot;,&quot;x&quot;))

`s.replace(&quot;r&quot;,&quot;x&quot;)` is indeed performed but it doesn&#39;t change the content of the stream.&lt;br&gt;
It is just a method-scoped `String` instance that is out of the scope after the invocation of `peek()`.


